This paper deals with the capacity limits of information propagation in mobile and Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs), which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also uses a stochastic model and analysis of encounter durations, which are common techniques in information theory (cs.IT) and stochastic processes (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the properties of journeys that maximize information propagation capacity, which can be seen as a problem in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides theoretical bounds on the information propagation speed, which can be seen as a problem in performance analysis and evaluation (cs.PF).
